Dr. Gresham is a physician in the Union hospital and Iola’s suitor. Dr. Gresham embodies one of the novel’s main conflicts, that between professing beliefs and living them through action. While he castigates slavery, advocates for blacks’ equal rights, and even vocally supports Dr. Latimer’s choice to publicly proclaim himself black, Dr. Gresham, a white man, will marry Iola only if she hides her identity as a mulatta woman and opts to pass as white.Read anin-depth analysis of Dr. Gresham.